node.title: Woman critically injured after being pinned against supermarket wall by car
node.description: The incident happened in the supermarket car park
node.content: ["A woman has been critically injured after being trapped between a car and the wall of a supermarket in west Auckland.", "\"Police and emergency services were called to Countdown in Te Atatu at around 11:20am after an elderly woman was hit by a vehicle in the carpark,\" a police spokesperson told Newshub.", "A St John spokesperson confirmed two ambulances, two rapid response units and one manager went to the scene.\u00a0", "\"St John assessed and treated one patient in a moderate condition at the scene and treated and transported one patient in a critical condition to Auckland City Hospital.\"", "The driver, who police describe as being \"very shaken by what has happened\", is assisting police with their enquiries.\u00a0"]
